      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000351",
          "label": "A.C. generator belt removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Water pump Belt removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000433",
          "label": "Water pump Belt removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Chain Case Cover Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2917_5.0_jpn_11582807_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Cam Chain Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2917_5.0_jpn_11582808_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Measure the skip length (A) of the cam chain tensioner."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the limit is exceeded, replace the cam chain and cam chain tensioner as a set."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Cam Chain Tensioner Flyout Length",
            "colspan": 2
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Limit value: 1"
          },
          {
            "text": "13.6mm"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Crankshaft pulley removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000368",
          "label": "Crankshaft pulley removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Chain Case Cover Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2917_5.0_jpn_11582809_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove old fluid packings, oil, and dirt from the chain case cover and chain case. Apply Honda Genuine Liquid Packing 1216E to the chain case contact surface of the chain case cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Apply liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 2.5 mm along the dashed line (A)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2917_5.0_jpn_11582810_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Install the chain case cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the liquid packing is left on for more than 4 minutes after application, do not install it as it is. Remove the packing once and reapply.",
        "Oil should be injected after at least 30 minutes after installation.",
        "Do not touch the liquid packing-applied surface.",
        "The engine should be started at least 3 hours after installation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Crankshaft pulley Installation",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000368",
          "label": "Crankshaft pulley Installation",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Front bumper removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000814",
          "label": "Front bumper removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. Front upper grille removal",
      "refs": [
